# Swap Event System Deep Dive

The Swap event system is a **decoupled event-driven architecture** for HTMX applications, allowing you to orchestrate UI updates without tight coupling between components.

---

## Core Concepts

### What is a Swap Event?

A **Swap Event** is a custom browser event triggered by server responses that tells HTMX elements when to update.

**Traditional approach (tightly coupled):**
```html
<!-- After adding todo, manually refresh list -->
<form hx-post="/Home/AddTodo" 
      hx-target="#todo-list">
</form>
```

**Swap event approach (decoupled):**
```html
<!-- Form fires event, list listens independently -->
<form hx-post="/Home/AddTodo"></form>

<div id="todo-list" 
     hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="entity.created:todo from:body">
</div>
```

**Benefits:**
- Components don't need to know about each other
- Multiple listeners can react to one action
- Easy to add new behaviors without touching existing code

---

## Event Naming Convention

Use **namespaced dot notation** for clarity:

```
category.action:entity
```

**Examples:**
- `entity.created:todo` — A todo was created
- `entity.updated:todo` — A todo was updated
- `entity.deleted:todo` — A todo was deleted
- `ui.refresh` — Generic UI refresh
- `ui.showToast` — Show toast notification
- `filter.changed:status` — Filter status changed

**Defining events in `Events/EventNames.cs`:**

```csharp
public static class SwapEvents
{
    public static class Entity
    {
        public static string Created(string name) => $"entity.created:{name}";
        public static string Updated(string name) => $"entity.updated:{name}";
        public static string Deleted(string name) => $"entity.deleted:{name}";
    }
    
    public static class UI
    {
        public const string Refresh = "ui.refresh";
        public const string ShowToast = "ui.showToast";
        public const string RefreshStats = "ui.refreshStats";
    }
    
    public static class Filter
    {
        public static string Changed(string name) => $"filter.changed:{name}";
    }
}
```

