## Event Chains

**Event chains** automatically fire secondary events when a primary event occurs.

### Defining Event Chains

**In `Events/SwapEventChains.cs`:**

```csharp
public static class SwapEventChains
{
    public static void Register(ISwapEvents events)
    {
        // When todo created → refresh UI + show toast
        events.Chain(
            SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"),
            SwapEvents.UI.Refresh,
            SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);
        
        // When todo updated → refresh UI + show toast
        events.Chain(
            SwapEvents.Entity.Updated("todo"),
            SwapEvents.UI.Refresh,
            SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);
        
        // When todo deleted → refresh UI + show toast + refresh stats
        events.Chain(
            SwapEvents.Entity.Deleted("todo"),
            SwapEvents.UI.Refresh,
            SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast,
            SwapEvents.UI.RefreshStats);
    }
}
```

### How Chains Work

When you fire `entity.created:todo` in a controller:

```csharp
_events.Fire(SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"));
```

The event chain automatically fires:
1. `entity.created:todo` (primary event)
2. `ui.refresh` (chained event)
3. `ui.showToast` (chained event)

**All listeners receive all events in the chain.**

