## Listening to Events in Views

### Basic Listener

```html
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="entity.created:todo from:body">
    <!-- List content -->
</div>
```

**Explanation:**
- `hx-trigger="entity.created:todo from:body"` — Listen for event on `<body>`
- When event fires → `hx-get="/Home/TodoList"` fetches updated list
- Response replaces `#todo-list` content

### Multiple Event Triggers

```html
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="entity.created:todo from:body, 
                 entity.updated:todo from:body,
                 entity.deleted:todo from:body">
</div>
```

Or use the chained event:

```html
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="ui.refresh from:body">
    <!-- Listens to ALL entity changes via chain -->
</div>
```

### Conditional Triggers

```html
<!-- Only refresh if not filtering -->
<div hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="ui.refresh from:body[!.filtering]">
</div>
```

### Delayed Triggers

```html
<!-- Wait 500ms before refreshing (debounce) -->
<div hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="ui.refresh from:body delay:500ms">
</div>
```

### Load + Event Trigger

```html
<!-- Load on page load AND when event fires -->
<div hx-get="/Home/Stats"
     hx-trigger="load, ui.refreshStats from:body">
</div>
```

