## Real-World Examples

### Product Management System

**EventNames.cs:**
```csharp
public static class ProductEvents
{
    public const string InventoryLow = "product.inventoryLow";
    public const string PriceChanged = "product.priceChanged";
}

public static class CartEvents
{
    public const string ItemAdded = "cart.itemAdded";
    public const string ItemRemoved = "cart.itemRemoved";
}
```

**SwapEventChains.cs:**
```csharp
events.Chain(
    SwapEvents.Entity.Created("product"),
    SwapEvents.UI.Refresh,
    SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);

events.Chain(
    ProductEvents.InventoryLow,
    SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast,
    SwapEvents.UI.RefreshStats);

events.Chain(
    CartEvents.ItemAdded,
    SwapEvents.UI.RefreshStats);
```

**Controller:**
```csharp
[HttpPost]
public IActionResult AddToCart(int productId)
{
    var product = _db.Products.Find(productId);
    // ... add to cart logic
    
    _events.Fire(CartEvents.ItemAdded);
    
    if (product.Stock < 5)
    {
        _events.Fire(ProductEvents.InventoryLow);
        _events.Toast(ToastType.Warning, "Low stock alert!");
    }
    
    return PartialView("_CartItem", cartItem);
}
```

**View:**
```html
<!-- Product list refreshes when inventory low -->
<div id="product-list"
     hx-get="/Products/List"
     hx-trigger="product.inventoryLow from:body">
</div>

<!-- Cart badge updates when items added/removed -->
<span id="cart-count"
      hx-get="/Cart/Count"
      hx-trigger="cart.itemAdded from:body, cart.itemRemoved from:body">
