## Custom Event Data

### Passing Data with Events

You can pass custom data via event detail:

**Controller:**
```csharp
_events.Fire("user.loggedIn", new { userId = user.Id, username = user.Name });
```

**JavaScript listener:**
```html
<script>
document.body.addEventListener('user.loggedIn', (e) => {
    console.log('User ID:', e.detail.userId);
    console.log('Username:', e.detail.username);
});
</script>
```

**Practical example — update user widget:**

```csharp
[HttpPost]
public IActionResult Login(string username, string password)
{
    var user = _db.Users.FirstOrDefault(u => u.Username == username);
    // ... auth logic
    
    _events.Fire("user.loggedIn", new { userId = user.Id, name = user.Name });
    
    return RedirectToAction("Index");
}
```

```html
<div id="user-widget"
     hx-get="/Account/Widget"
     hx-trigger="user.loggedIn from:body">
</div>
```

