## Performance Considerations

### Avoid Event Storms

**Bad (causes infinite loop):**
```html
<div hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="ui.refresh from:body"
     hx-swap="innerHTML"
     hx-on::after-swap="htmx.trigger('body', 'ui.refresh')">
    <!-- Fires ui.refresh after swap, causing infinite loop -->
</div>
```

**Good:**
```html
<div hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="ui.refresh from:body">
    <!-- Only listens, doesn't fire -->
</div>
```

### Debounce Rapid Events

```html
<!-- Wait 500ms after last event -->
<div hx-get="/Search/Results"
     hx-trigger="filter.changed:search from:body delay:500ms">
</div>
```

### Limit Chain Depth

**Bad (too many chains):**
```csharp
events.Chain(
    "event1", "event2", "event3", "event4", "event5", "event6");
```

Keep chains to **2-4 events** for maintainability.

### Use Specific Events Over Generic

**Bad:**
```csharp
_events.Fire("ui.refresh"); // Too generic, many listeners fire
```

**Good:**
```csharp
_events.Fire("ui.refreshTodoList"); // Specific, only todo list updates
```

