## Best Practices

✅ **Do:**
- Use namespaced naming (`entity.created:todo`, not `todoCreated`)
- Define all event names in `EventNames.cs`
- Keep event chains simple (2-4 events max)
- Use specific events over generic ones
- Document event flows in `SwapEventChains.cs`

❌ **Don't:**
- Hard-code event names in views (use constants)
- Create circular event chains
- Fire too many events from one action
- Use events for synchronous logic (use method calls)
- Forget to register chains in `SwapEventChains.cs`

