## Advanced Patterns

### Conditional Event Chains

```csharp
public static void Register(ISwapEvents events)
{
    events.Chain(
        SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"),
        SwapEvents.UI.Refresh);
    
    // Only in production
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT") == "Production")
    {
        events.Chain(
            SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"),
            "analytics.track");
    }
}
```

### Event Aggregation

Combine multiple events into one:

```csharp
public static class AggregatedEvents
{
    public const string DataChanged = "data.changed";
}

events.Chain(SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"), AggregatedEvents.DataChanged);
events.Chain(SwapEvents.Entity.Updated("todo"), AggregatedEvents.DataChanged);
events.Chain(SwapEvents.Entity.Deleted("todo"), AggregatedEvents.DataChanged);
```

Listeners use single event:

```html
<div hx-get="/Dashboard/Summary"
     hx-trigger="data.changed from:body">
</div>
```

### Event Priority

Fire critical events first:

```csharp
_events.Fire(SwapEvents.Entity.Deleted("todo")); // Primary
_events.Fire(SwapEvents.UI.RefreshStats); // Critical
_events.Fire(SwapEvents.UI.Refresh); // Secondary
```

